21 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Statute of limitations for surety bonds. (1) On an action relating to a
22 surety appearance bond, the period to commence an action is 2 years. The 2-year period begins on the date
23 the bond is executed.
24 (2) The surety appearance bond must be exonerated and discharged after 2 years, regardless of
25 the status of the court case, unless otherwise agreed on by the surety bail bond agent.
26 (3) Courts may require a defendant to:
27 (a) post a new bond if the case continues beyond 2 years and the court determines that continued
28 bond security is necessary; and
