22 peace or a court in the county of arrest without unnecessary delay.
23 (a) At the hearing, the court or justice of the peace must:
24 (i) inform the defendant of the charges and conditions outlined in the warrant;
25 (ii) confirm the identity of the defendant as the individual named in the warrant; and
26 (iii) notify the defendant of their right to post bond as specified in the warrant or await transfer to
