5 NEW SECTION. Section 17. Automatic bond discharge -- exoneration for defendants released
6 to own recognizance. (1) An existing bond for a defendant in the same jurisdiction must be automatically
7 discharged and exonerated if:
8 (a) the defendant is arrested on new charges or a separate warrant unrelated to the charges
9 covered by the existing bond; and
10 (b) the court orders the defendant's release on their own recognizance or for the new charges or
11 warrant.
12 (2) Courts may not:
13 (a) hold a surety bail bond agent liable for a secured bond when the defendant is considered
14 appropriate for release on their own recognizance; or
15 (b) use an existing bond to justify liability for unrelated charges while simultaneously granting own-
16 recognizance release on new charges.
17 (3) The legislature intends for these provisions to:
18 (a) prevent inequities in which courts grant own-recognizance releases for some charges but retain
19 secured bond liability for unrelated charges; and
20 (b) align the court's determination of the defendant's risk with the financial liability of the surety bail
21 bond agent.
22 (4) Courts shall:
23 (a) exonerate any existing bond for a defendant in the same jurisdiction when an own-
24 recognizance release is granted, whether explicitly requested by the surety or not; and
25 (b) provide written notice to the surety bail bond agent confirming the exoneration and discharge of
26 liability.
